From 107b6769eb5841a117f361164ca93dda95a1830f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcus Figueiredo <figueiredo@protonmail.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 13:28:01 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] gfxstream: fix host GLES decoder build on macOS, select
 native EGL backend

The composer3 HAL's HWC3 implementation needs the legacy renderControl/GLES
HostConnection path (libOpenglSystemCommon -> lib_renderControl_enc.so),
which requires a GLES-capable gfxstream host backend. This repo's
libgfxstream_backend.dylib was Vulkan-only (-Ddecoders=vulkan), so that RPC
never got a response and composer3 hung forever in queryHostExtensions
waiting on a reply that would never arrive (see prior commit's note).

This was assumed to be a platform limitation (NSOpenGL deprecated/removed
on modern macOS), since the project deliberately chose Vulkan-only.
Verified by actually trying -Ddecoders=vulkan,gles,composer: that
assumption was wrong. NSOpenGL still exists on this macOS version, and
egl_os_api_darwin.cpp/mac_native.m already implement a complete native
Darwin EGL/GL backend. The real blockers were build bugs in this vendored
tree's host/frame_buffer.cpp and host/meson.build, never exercised before
because nothing had built with GLES enabled here.

host/frame_buffer.cpp (6 bugs, all from code added under
`#if GFXSTREAM_ENABLE_HOST_GLES` that duplicated or broke existing
definitions):
- getEmulatedEglWindowSurfaceColorBufferHandle: missing closing brace on
  the not-found branch -- the `if` body never closed before `return
  it->second`, so the function's own closing brace only closed the `if`.
- setScreenMask, createTrivialContext, getDeviceInfo: each duplicated
  verbatim inside a `#if GFXSTREAM_ENABLE_HOST_GLES` block despite an
  identical (or, for createTrivialContext, properly #if/#else-guarded)
  definition already existing elsewhere in the file -- redefinition
  errors with GLES enabled. Removed the redundant copies.
- FrameBuffer::getConfigs: the pImpl-forwarding wrapper was missing
  entirely (only FrameBuffer::Impl::getConfigs existed), leaving
  render_control.cpp's call to FrameBuffer::getConfigs undefined at link
  time. Added it, matching the neighboring forwarders' pattern.

host/meson.build:
- The gfxstream_backend library() target passed cpp_args but never
  objcpp_args, so .mm (Objective-C++) sources never received
  -DGFXSTREAM_ENABLE_HOST_GLES. native_sub_window_metal.mm's
  `#if !GFXSTREAM_ENABLE_HOST_GLES` guard therefore always saw the macro
  as undefined (i.e. always true) and compiled its Vulkan-only
  createSubWindow/destroySubWindow/moveSubWindow/getNativeDisplay
  unconditionally, clashing with native_sub_window_cocoa.mm's versions
  once the GLES decoder pulled cocoa.mm into the same build. Added
  objcpp_args. Also added the macOS frameworks (OpenGL, IOSurface,
  CoreVideo) that mac_native.m's direct NSOpenGL/CGL calls need, gated on
  use_gles since the Vulkan-only build doesn't touch them.

host/native_sub_window_metal.mm:
- getMetalLayerFromView duplicated across cocoa.mm (for the
  EmuGLViewWithMetal view type cocoa.mm creates, used once GLES is
  enabled) and metal.mm (for the EmuMetalView type metal.mm's own
  Vulkan-only createSubWindow creates). Guarded metal.mm's copy with
  the same `#if !GFXSTREAM_ENABLE_HOST_GLES` as the functions it serves.

With these 6 fixes, `meson setup -Ddecoders=vulkan,gles,composer && ninja`
builds and links libgfxstream_backend.dylib cleanly on macOS arm64.

vendor/libkrun/src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/virtio_gpu.rs:
- create_rutabaga_gfxstream: flip use_gles from false to true (matches the
  rebuilt dylib) and use_egl from false to... still false, deliberately.
  STREAM_RENDERER_FLAGS_USE_EGL_BIT maps to gfxstream's `EglOnEgl` feature
  (virtio_gpu_gfxstream_renderer.cpp's ParseGfxstreamFeatures), which makes
  EglGlobalInfo route through egl_os_api_egl.cpp's
  getEgl2EglHostInstance() -- a passthrough that dlopen()s a host
  libEGL.so/libGLESv2.so. Those don't exist on macOS (confirmed via the
  dlopen failure messages when use_egl was tried as true). With
  use_egl(false), EglGlobalInfo's `else` branch picks
  EglOS::Engine::createHostInstance(), i.e. egl_os_api_darwin.cpp's actual
  native NSOpenGL/CGL implementation -- the one this platform has.
  use_gles(true) is unaffected by this and still enables the GLES
  decoder/capset gfxstream reports to the guest.

Result: gfxstream now initializes through the native Darwin EGL path with
no dlopen errors, and Vulkan device selection proceeds normally
(Apple M2, externalMemoryMode: Metal). Diagnosed but not yet fixed: a
texture_draw.cpp GLES shader fails to compile for the guest framebuffer
blit path, and the host process crashes shortly after with no Rust panic
message (native/Obj-C crash, not yet isolated). composer3/boot completion
with the GLES decoder is still blocked on this.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/virtio_gpu.rs   | 18 ++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/vendor/libkrun/src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/virtio_gpu.rs b/vendor/libkrun/src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/virtio_gpu.rs
index 284cb3a..2c01c45 100644
--- a/vendor/libkrun/src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/virtio_gpu.rs
+++ b/vendor/libkrun/src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/virtio_gpu.rs
@@ -317,9 +317,19 @@ impl VirtioGpu {
         display_width: u32,
         display_height: u32,
     ) -> Option<Rutabaga> {
-        // Vulkan-only: configure via RutabagaBuilder fluent API.
-        // GFXSTREAM_ENABLE_HOST_GLES=0 means EGL/GLES are unavailable;
-        // use_vulkan(true) is the only meaningful flag here.
+        // Vulkan + GLES (composer3's renderControl path needs a real GLES
+        // decoder on the host; gfxstream is built with -Ddecoders=vulkan,gles).
+        //
+        // use_egl(false) is deliberate even though GLES is enabled:
+        // STREAM_RENDERER_FLAGS_USE_EGL_BIT maps to gfxstream's `EglOnEgl`
+        // feature, which routes the GLES translator through `egl_os_api_egl.cpp`
+        // -- a passthrough that dlopen()s a host libEGL.so/libGLESv2.so. Those
+        // don't exist on macOS (no native EGL). With EglOnEgl off,
+        // EglGlobalInfo picks the native Darwin backend instead
+        // (egl_os_api_darwin.cpp's `Engine::createHostInstance()`, built on
+        // mac_native.m's direct NSOpenGL/CGL calls) -- the one this platform
+        // actually has. `use_gles(true)` is unaffected by this and still
+        // enables the GLES decoder/capset.
         let builder = RutabagaBuilder::new(
             rutabaga_gfx::RutabagaComponentType::Gfxstream,
             0, // virgl_flags — unused by gfxstream component
@@ -328,7 +338,7 @@ impl VirtioGpu {
         .set_display_width(display_width)
         .set_display_height(display_height)
         .set_use_egl(false)
-        .set_use_gles(false)
+        .set_use_gles(true)
         .set_use_glx(false)
         .set_use_surfaceless(false)
         .set_use_vulkan(true)
-- 
